# Bools

Why bools in most languages waste 7 bits of space:

// Why can't c just add lambdas
bool deref(const bool* bp) {
	return *bp
}

>>> make
>>> ./a.out
*** SEGMENTATION FAULT *** (core dumped)
Cannot dereference pointer "0xFFFF.b": Sits halfway inbetween 2 bits (0xFFFF.a and 0xFFFF.c)
This may be caused by floating-point imprecision, or a glitch
>>> google-chrome & >/dev/null 2>/dev/null

<Title Text>:
Never dereference /.*\.[13579bBdDfF]/
